        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Ending Debt Collection Harassment Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill prohibits a debt collector from sending electronic communications to a consumer without the consumer's consent. The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) may not issue rules that allow a debt collector to send unlimited electronic communications. Additionally, the CFPB must report on consumer complaints about electronic communications and enforcement actions taken against debt collectors. </p>]]></text>
